{{refbegin}}
:{{note label|SpecialElection|1|1}} This table does not include [[By-election|special elections]], which may be held to fill political offices that have become vacant between the regularly scheduled elections.
:{{note label|HouseDelegates|2|2}} As well as all six [[Non-voting members of the United States House of Representatives|non-voting delegates]] of the U.S. House.
:{{note label|HousePR|3|3}} As well as five [[Non-voting members of the United States House of Representatives|non-voting delegates]] of the U.S. House. The [[Resident Commissioner of Puerto Rico]] instead serves a four-year term that coincides with the presidential term.
:{{note label|NEandVTGovs|4|4}} The Governors of New Hampshire and Vermont are each elected to two-year terms. The other 48 state governors and all five territorial governors serve four-year terms.
